        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "Scalar functions can have performance implications when used in large queries, especially if they are called repeatedly for each row in a result set. This is because scalar functions are executed row-by-row, which can lead to slower query performance compared to set-based operations. It is important to consider the context in which the function is used and to test its impact on query performance."
